<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4635104>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 5. Reflected-light photographs of Gromia melinus sp. nov. from station 809, at 3103-m depth (A–C), and station 819, at 4392-m depth (D); photographed in water. A, paratype, reg. no. SMF XXVII 7401, subtriangular morphotype. B, holotype, reg. no. SMF XXVII 7400, droplet-shaped morphotype. C, asymmetrically irregular morphotype. D, spherical morphotype with two oral capsules. E, scanning electron microscope (SEM) photograph of the polygonal pattern on the wall surface. F, SEM photograph of agglutinated clay particles on the surface of the specimen." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4635104/files/figure.png" .

